<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-15T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="32" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G/277: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                            Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-15T10:00:00-04:00">October 15, 1933—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>95. Referring further to Department’s telegram No. 76, October 10, 7
                                p.m., in informal conversation with Undersecretary of Foreign
                                Affairs last night he said <hi rend="italic">Prensa</hi> editorial
                                did not reflect views of his Government. That as regards the
                                Montevideo Conference, Argentina was “at the orders” of the
                                Uruguayan Government and that in his opinion it was now too late to
                                think of postponement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>